    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-12-15T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-12-15T19:00:00-05:00" n="151"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d151">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867.00/12–1448: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Turkey</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-12-15T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 15, 1948—7 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>589. <gloss target="#t_Patsu1">Patsu</gloss> 122. Re <gloss target="#t_Ustap1"
                        >Ustap</gloss> 150.<note n="1" xml:id="d151fn1">Identified also as telegram
                        881, December 14, from Ankara, not printed.</note> $50,000,000 have been
                    allocated Turkey from <gloss target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 49 funds (<gloss
                        target="#t_Patsu1">Patsu</gloss> 114<note n="2" xml:id="d151fn2">Identified
                        also as telegram 519, October 25, to Ankara, not printed.</note>). With
                    Ambassador Grady’s concurrence, Dept recommended to Sec Def additional
                    $25,000,000 be allocated, bringing total Turkish allocation <gloss
                        target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 49 to $75,000,000. Prompt approval Sec Def
                        anticipated.<note n="3" xml:id="d151fn3">Secretary Forrestal’s approval was
                        given in his letter of December 23 to the Secretary of State
                        (867.00/12–2348).</note>
                </p>
                <p>Dept and Army consider unnecessary any departure present policy of withholding
                    info concerning division <gloss target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 49 Aid funds between
                    Greece and Turkey, since such info might provide basis for comparison and
                    comment producing an unfortunate reaction. Moreover, funds allocated Turkey but
                    unobligated might have to be diverted to Greek program in unforeseen emergency.
                    For these reasons Dept and Army prefer avoid specific statement re division
                    Greek-Turkish funds.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
